          items={[
            {
              title: t('faq.q1.title', 'Is {{appShortName}} free to use?'),
              content: t(
                'faq.q1.answer',
                'Yes. The core framework is open-source under the MIT license. We offer premium support and managed hosting for teams that need it.'
              ),
            },
            {
              title: t('faq.q2.title', 'What backends are supported?'),
              content: t(
                'faq.q2.answer',
                'Firebase, Supabase, and Vercel are supported out of the box. The architecture is provider-agnostic, so adding a custom backend is straightforward.'
              ),
            },
            {
              title: t('faq.q3.title', 'Can I use it for an existing project?'),
              content: t(
                'faq.q3.answer',
                'Absolutely. Each package is independent and can be adopted incrementally. Start with the component library or the CRUD module and expand from there.'
              ),
            },
            {
              title: t('faq.q4.title', 'How does it handle scaling?'),
              content: t(
                'faq.q4.answer',
                'The framework is designed for serverless-first architecture. Functions scale to zero when idle and auto-scale under load. No infrastructure management required.'
              ),
            },
            {
              title: t('faq.q5.title', 'Is there a component library?'),
              content: t(
                'faq.q5.answer',
                'Yes. Over 60 production-ready components with full accessibility, theming, responsive behavior, and RTL support. All documented with live examples.'
              ),
            },
            {
              title: t('faq.q6.title', 'What about mobile?'),
              content: t(
                'faq.q6.answer',
                'Web apps are fully responsive by default. For native mobile, we provide an Expo template with shared business logic and consistent design tokens.'
              ),
            },
